1. On dev, update the version number to a release version without a dev
   component.
2. Update cff file release date, version, and notes (dropping dev component).
3. Consolidate inst/NEWS.Rd and run make.
4. Commit changes to DESCRIPTION, codemeta.json, news files and docs.
5. Checkout main (git checkout main).
6. Merge changes (git merge dev) and resolve conflicts, if any, and commit.
7. Delete cassettes, run tests and commit changes to test assets.
8. Rebuild README (touch README.Rmd; make) and commit.
8. Check winbuilder (`devtools::check_win_devel()`) and rhub
   (`devtools::check_rhub()`).
9. Update and commit cran-comments.md.
10. Release (`devtools::release()`) and wait for CRAN response.
11. Once CRAN version goes online (news file in particular) rebuild pkgdown
    docs (touch _pkgdown.yml; make), commit changes and CRAN-SUBMISSION file,
    and push.
12. On GitHub, tag as new release and copy NEWS.md updates.
13. Remove CRAN-SUBMISSION and then commit.
14. Checkout dev (`git checkout dev`).
15. Merge main (`git merge main`).
16. Add dev component to version number, delete cassettes, rerun tests,
    update cff, news and docs, commit and push.
